er%20of%20Hamas%20in%20August%20after%20the%20death%20of%20his%20predecessor%2C%20Ismail%20Haniyeh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Israel%20has%20hailed%20Sinwar's%20killing%20as%20a%20major%20win%2C%20analysts%20say%20Hamas%20could%20use%20his%20legacy%20to%20mobilise%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20militants%2C%20who%20grew%20up%20suffering%20the%20consequences%20of%20Israel's%20retaliatory%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20a%20look%20at%20what%20could%20come%20next%20for%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20harsh%20a%20blow%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConfirming%20Sinwar's%20death%20in%20a%20video%20statement%20on%20Friday%2C%20Hamas%20official%20Khalil%20al-Hayya%20said%20the%20group%20was%20mourning%20the%20loss%20of%20its%20%26quot%3Bgreat%20leader%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESinwar's%20killing%20was%20not%20just%20%26quot%3Ban%20extremely%20symbolic%20event%26quot%3B%20but%20created%20%26quot%3Ba%20leadership%20vacuum%20in%20this%20very%20networked%20organisation%26quot%3B%2C%20Middle%20East%20analyst%20Andreas%20Krieg%20of%20King's%20College%20London%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20death%20comes%20little%20more%20than%20two%20months%20after%20the%20death%20in%20Iran%20of%20Hamas's%20political%20chief%20Ismail%20Haniyeh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHamas%20and%20Iran%20have%20blamed%20Israel%20for%20Haniyeh's%20death%2C%20though%20Israel%20has%20not%20offered%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrieg%20said%20differences%20had%20emerged%20between%20Hamas's%20political%20leadership%2C%20in%20exile%20mostly%20in%20Qatar%2C%20and%20the%20military%20and%20operational%20wings%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%20Israel%20also%20said%20it%20killed%20Hamas%20military%20chief%20Mohammed%20Deif%20in%20Gaza%2C%20which%20Hamas%20has%20denied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDifferent%20cells%20of%20Hamas%20will%20continue%20fighting%2C%20but%20at%20the%20core%20of%20the%20movement%2C%20there's%20a%20vacuum%20there%2C%20and%20that%20will%20make%20it%20very%20difficult%20to%20coordinate%2C%26quot%3B%20Krieg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJames%20Dorsey%2C%20of%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore's%20Middle%20East%20Institute%2C%20said%20Sinwar%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Bexceptional%26quot%3B%20figure%20in%20Hamas%20who%20enjoyed%20%26quot%3Bbroad%20support%20within%20the%20movement%20from%20both%20the%20political%20and%20the%20military%20wing%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20could%20replace%20Sinwar%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20his%20predecessor's%20death%2C%20Sinwar%20emerged%20from%20a%20field%20of%20contenders%20for%20the%20Hamas%20leadership%20that%20included%20relative%20moderates%20based%20outside%20of%20Gaza%20like%20Musa%20Abu%20Marzuk%2C%20an%20adviser%20and%20negotiator%20seen%20as%20close%20to%20Haniyeh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDorsey%20said%20other%20exiled%20Hamas%20figures%20like%20Qatar-based%20Hayya%2C%20close%20to%20Sinwar%20and%20lead%20negotiator%20in%20unsuccessful%20talks%20for%20a%20Gaza%20truce%20and%20hostage%20exchange%2C%20could%20once%20again%20become%20contenders%20for%20the%20top%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20exiled%20leaders%20who%20could%20take%20over%2C%20he%20said%2C%20include%20Khaled%20Meshaal%2C%20who%20served%20as%20Hamas%20chief%20until%20he%20was%20replaced%20by%20Haniyeh%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESinwar's%20selection%20as%20leader%20over%20members%20of%20its%20political%20wing%20in%20August%20was%20widely%20viewed%20as%20a%20restructuring%20of%20the%20movement%20around%20armed%20struggle%2C%20with%20the%20focus%20on%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrieg%20said%20%26quot%3Bthe%20next%20leader%20is%20inevitably%20going%20to%20be%20someone%20from%20the%20operational%20level%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShould%20the%20leadership%20be%20handed%20to%20a%20man%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%20one%20name%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20favourite%3A%20that%20of%20Sinwar's%20younger%20brother%20Mohammed%20Sinwar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C